  "commentary": "With SPX at 6940.59 in PIN regime and sitting just below the massive 6950 gamma wall (+18.6B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher as they hedge their long gamma exposure. The strong positive GEX profile above current levels (6940, 6950, 7000 strikes all showing heavy stabilizing gamma) suggests dealers will cap upside momentum through systematic selling, while the recent 2.4% 5-minute move likely triggered some of this hedging flow already. Watch 6950 as the key resistance level where dealer selling intensifies, with 6900 providing downside support if we retrace.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get capped near 6950 with choppy action between 6900-6950.",
